        "mock_article": {
          "title": "Modernist Art in the New Century: Reconsidering the Archive",
          "author": "Alireza Parsa",
          "date": "October 6, 2024",
          "sidebar_items": [
            "Roots of Minimalist Design",
            "Impact of Typography on Visual Perception",
            "The Future of Digital Archives"
          ],
          "lead": "In today's fast-paced world, the concept of the archive has transformed from a dusty warehouse to a living and dynamic institution. In this writing, we explore how Iranian modernism has established a bridge between calligraphy traditions and today's digital needs.",
          "body_p1": "Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry's standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book.",
          "figure_caption": "Figure 1: Visualization of color movement in empty space; inspiring minimalist design.",
          "section_title": "Return to Roots",
          "body_p2": "Typography is not only a tool for conveying meaning, but also a form of art rooted in the depths of our history. The use of Nastaliq lines in modern user interface environments is a challenge faced by contemporary designers. In 'Archive', we strive to bridge this gap using new web standards and optimized Persian fonts.",
          "quote": "Good design is not only seen, but felt. Archive is a collection of emotions recorded in the form of shape and color.",
          "quote_author": "Morteza Momayez",
          "body_p3": "Ultimately, our goal in gathering this collection is to create a space for thinking and reconsidering cultural assets. Every piece in this archive has a story to tell, and every article is a window to a deeper understanding of modern aesthetics.",
          "related": [
            {
              "title": "Impact of Bauhaus on Iranian Contemporary Architecture",
              "category": "editorial"
            },
            {
              "title": "Calligraphy Tradition in the Digital Age",
              "category": "curation"
            },
            {
              "title": "How to Build an Art Collection?",
              "category": "archive"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "articles": {
        "featured": {
          "title": "Modernist Revival: How Simplicity Reclaimed the World",
          "excerpt": "In today's noisy world, returning to the fundamentals of design and architecture is not a choice, but a necessity. In this issue, we explore why pure forms endure.",
          "date": "June 4, 2024"
        },
        "1": {
          "title": "Ten Designers Who Pushed Digital Boundaries",
          "excerpt": "A look at pioneering works in motion typography and visual interactions this year.",
